39
00:01:56,383 --> 00:02:00,521 line:-2
after I went to--
after the panic attack,


40
00:02:00.554 --> 00:02:01.855 line:-1 align:center
I went to go see a doctor,


41
00:02:01,889 --> 00:02:04,558 line:-2
and he asked me
a bunch of questions.


42
00:02:04,591 --> 00:02:06,560 line:-2
And one of the questions
was, "Do you do drugs?"


43
00:02:06.593 --> 00:02:09.196 line:-2 align:center
And I kind of sheepishly
said, "Yeah, I do."


44
00:02:09,229 --> 00:02:10,898 line:-1
And he gave me a look


45
00:02:10.931 --> 00:02:14.635 line:-2 align:center
that indicated, "OK, moron.
Mystery solved."


46
00:02:14,668 --> 00:02:16,737 line:-2
And he pointed out
that even though the drug use


47
00:02:16.770 --> 00:02:18.705 line:-1 align:center
was somewhat unspectacular,


48
00:02:18,739 --> 00:02:20,507 line:-2
it was enough
to change my brain chemistry


49
00:02:20.541 --> 00:02:23.844 line:-2 align:center
and make it more likely
for me to freak out.


50
00:02:23,877 --> 00:02:26,246 line:-2
So this was
a huge ‘Aha!’ moment for me,


51
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:28,749 line:-2
and I decided to quit
doing drugs


52
00:02:28.782 --> 00:02:33.120 line:-2 align:center
and to go see this shrink once
or twice a week indefinitely.


53
00:02:33,153 --> 00:02:36,790 line:-2
I started to poke around
and realized that there was


54
00:02:36,823 --> 00:02:41,028 line:-2
a lot of evidence that suggested
that meditation


55
00:02:41.061 --> 00:02:42.996 line:-2 align:center
was really good for you,
that it could lower


56
00:02:43.030 --> 00:02:44.631 line:-2 align:center
your blood pressure,
boost your immune system,


57
00:02:44.665 --> 00:02:46.834 line:-2 align:center
literally rewire
key parts of your brain.


58
00:02:46.867 --> 00:02:48.769 line:-1 align:center
And there was at this time


59
00:02:48,802 --> 00:02:52,506 line:-2
a not very well-publicized
body of research


60
00:02:52.539 --> 00:02:54.274 line:-2 align:center
that strongly suggested
that meditation


61
00:02:54.308 --> 00:02:56.944 line:-2 align:center
was really good for you,
so I started to try it,


62
00:02:56.977 --> 00:02:59.880 line:-2 align:center
and I started with, like,
five or ten minutes a day.


63
00:02:59.913 --> 00:03:02.449 line:-2 align:center
And I found that there
were really three main benefits.


64
00:03:03.750 --> 00:03:06.687 line:-2 align:center
The first benefit
is that it made me calmer.


65
00:03:06.720 --> 00:03:09.456 line:-2 align:center
Now, I want to be careful
about this word, "calm."


66
00:03:09,489 --> 00:03:12,092 line:-2
Because some people sit
and meditate, and they expect


67
00:03:12.125 --> 00:03:14.595 line:-2 align:center
to feel calm immediately
and that if they don't,


68
00:03:14.628 --> 00:03:15.929 line:-2 align:center
they feel like
they're a failed meditator.


69
00:03:15.963 --> 00:03:17.431 line:-1 align:center
That's not quite how it works.


70
00:03:17,464 --> 00:03:18,665 line:-2
Just because
you sit to meditate,


71
00:03:18.699 --> 00:03:22.736 line:-2 align:center
you are not necessarily
going to get calm lickety-split.


72
00:03:22.769 --> 00:03:24.872 line:-2 align:center
But the cumulative effect
of taking myself


73
00:03:24.905 --> 00:03:28.075 line:-2 align:center
out of the traffic
for five minutes every day


74
00:03:28.108 --> 00:03:30.511 line:-1 align:center
just injected my overall life


75
00:03:30,544 --> 00:03:33,080 line:-2
with a little bit
more calm and sanity.


76
00:03:33.113 --> 00:03:35.916 line:-2 align:center
The second benefit
is that it helped me with focus.


77
00:03:37,684 --> 00:03:40,053 line:-2
As you'll see in a minute,
meditation,


78
00:03:40.087 --> 00:03:43.490 line:-2 align:center
the practice of meditation
is generally where you just try


79
00:03:43,524 --> 00:03:45,659 line:-2
to pick one thing
to pay attention to,


80
00:03:45.692 --> 00:03:47.227 line:-2 align:center
usually the feeling of
your breath coming in


81
00:03:47.261 --> 00:03:49.029 line:-2 align:center
or going out,
and then every time


82
00:03:49.062 --> 00:03:50.531 line:-2 align:center
you get distracted,
you start again


83
00:03:50.564 --> 00:03:52.332 line:-1 align:center
and again and again.


84
00:03:52,366 --> 00:03:54,401 line:-2
And every time you do that,
it's like a bicep curl


85
00:03:54.434 --> 00:03:55.836 line:-1 align:center
for your brain.


86
00:03:55.869 --> 00:03:58.105 line:-2 align:center
And this has been shown
on brain scans


87
00:03:58.138 --> 00:03:59.907 line:-1 align:center
to change the area of the brain


88
00:03:59,940 --> 00:04:01,675 line:-2
associated
with attention regulation,


89
00:04:01.708 --> 00:04:05.112 line:-2 align:center
and I really found
that in my hectic life


90
00:04:05,145 --> 00:04:07,915 line:-2
where I actually have
other people's voices


91
00:04:07,948 --> 00:04:11,552 line:-2
piped directly into my head
as a news anchor,


92
00:04:11,585 --> 00:04:13,420 line:-2
it really helped me…
meditation…


93
00:04:13.453 --> 00:04:15.656 line:-2 align:center
it really helped me
to stay on task.


94
00:04:15.689 --> 00:04:17.824 line:-2 align:center
The third benefit
is the most important one,


95
00:04:17.858 --> 00:04:20.127 line:-2 align:center
and it's a word
that is thrown around


96
00:04:20.160 --> 00:04:21.128 line:-1 align:center
a lot these days.


97
00:04:21.161 --> 00:04:23.130 line:-2 align:center
It's become
somewhat of a buzz phrase,


98
00:04:23.163 --> 00:04:25.666 line:-1 align:center
and it's mindfulness.


99
00:04:26.934 --> 00:04:30.370 line:-2 align:center
Mindfulness is,
just to put it very simply,


100
00:04:30,404 --> 00:04:33,907 line:-2
it's the skill
that allows you to notice


101
00:04:33,941 --> 00:04:35,309 line:-1
what's happening in your head


102
00:04:35.342 --> 00:04:39.046 line:-2 align:center
at any given moment without
getting carried away by it.


103
00:04:39.079 --> 00:04:40.480 line:-2 align:center
I'm just going to--I'm just
going to say that again


104
00:04:40,514 --> 00:04:42,382 line:-2
because this is really
the most important point.


105
00:04:42.416 --> 00:04:44.818 line:-2 align:center
Mindfulness is the ability,
the kind of self-awareness


106
00:04:44,852 --> 00:04:46,386 line:-2
that allows you to notice
what's happening


107
00:04:46.420 --> 00:04:48.322 line:-2 align:center
in your body
and in your mind


108
00:04:48,355 --> 00:04:50,123 line:-2
without necessarily
taking the bait


109
00:04:50.157 --> 00:04:51.558 line:-1 align:center
and acting on it.


110
00:04:51,592 --> 00:04:54,494 line:-2
So, for example,
I would notice that I would be


111
00:04:54.528 --> 00:04:55.963 line:-2 align:center
in a conversation
with my wife,


112
00:04:55.996 --> 00:04:57.531 line:-1 align:center
maybe things weren't going well.


113
00:04:57,564 --> 00:04:59,900 line:-2
I would notice, "Oh, yeah,
I'm starting to get angry,"


114
00:04:59.933 --> 00:05:01.468 line:-2 align:center
but I don't have
to say something


115
00:05:01.502 --> 00:05:04.171 line:-2 align:center
that's gonna ruin
the next 48 hours of my life.


116
00:05:04.204 --> 00:05:06.240 line:-1 align:center
Or maybe I'm bored or lonely


117
00:05:06.273 --> 00:05:08.775 line:-2 align:center
and I see a zombie arm
reaching into the cabinet


118
00:05:08.809 --> 00:05:12.980 line:-2 align:center
