195
00:08:52.065 --> 00:08:55.435 line:-2 align:center
Exercise,
healthy eating--


196
00:08:55.469 --> 00:08:58.805 line:-2 align:center
without getting
too obsessive about it,


197
00:08:58.839 --> 00:09:00.274 line:-2 align:center
so I think it's important
to eat healthy


198
00:09:00.307 --> 00:09:02.676 line:-2 align:center
but not to the point
where you're obsessing


199
00:09:02.709 --> 00:09:04.711 line:-2 align:center
about what you're eating
all the time.


200
00:09:04,745 --> 00:09:09,283 line:-2
The fourth thing I would
say is nature, access to nature.


201
00:09:09.316 --> 00:09:13.153 line:-2 align:center
There's a ton of data
that strongly indicate


202
00:09:13.187 --> 00:09:16.690 line:-2 align:center
that if you are getting
consistent access to nature


203
00:09:16.723 --> 00:09:19.326 line:-2 align:center
that it's going to have
all sorts of physiological


204
00:09:19,359 --> 00:09:20,727 line:-1
and psychological benefits.


205
00:09:20.761 --> 00:09:22.196 line:-2 align:center
And then finally,
