Do we need a haircut?


528
00:24:31.271 --> 00:24:32.840 line:-1 align:center
Blah, blah, blah…


529
00:24:32,873 --> 00:24:38,212 line:-2
And a lot of people feel or fear
that when they get distracted


530
00:24:38,245 --> 00:24:40,714 line:-2
in this way,
when they sit and meditate


531
00:24:40.747 --> 00:24:42.983 line:-2 align:center
and notice
that working with the mind


532
00:24:43.016 --> 00:24:45.919 line:-2 align:center
is a little bit like holding
a live fish in your hand,


533
00:24:45,953 --> 00:24:48,956 line:-2
a lot of people
tell themselves a story


534
00:24:48.989 --> 00:24:50.724 line:-2 align:center
that,
"Oh, I'm a failed meditator.


535
00:24:50,757 --> 00:24:52,192 line:-1
I can never do this."


536
00:24:52,226 --> 00:24:55,229 line:-2
And that's because there's this
really pernicious misconception


537
00:24:55.262 --> 00:24:58.765 line:-2 align:center
that correct meditation
involves clearing your mind.


538
00:25:00.000 --> 00:25:02.569 line:-2 align:center
As I like to joke,
clearing your mind


539
00:25:02,603 --> 00:25:04,238 line:-2
isn't possible
unless you're enlightened


540
00:25:04.271 --> 00:25:05.672 line:-1 align:center
or you've died.


541
00:25:05,706 --> 00:25:08,108 line:-2
The whole game in meditation
is to notice


542
00:25:08,141 --> 00:25:11,979 line:-2
when you've become distracted…
again and again and again…


543
00:25:12.012 --> 00:25:13.213 line:-1 align:center
and just start over,


544
00:25:13,247 --> 00:25:16,116 line:-2
and this is the bicep curl
for your brain,


545
00:25:16,149 --> 00:25:17,451 line:-1
and this is what shows up


546
00:25:17.484 --> 00:25:20.220 line:-2 align:center
on the brain scans
of meditators.


547
00:25:21.555 --> 00:25:23.357 line:-2 align:center
So I just want to--
and by the way,


548
00:25:23,390 --> 00:25:24,892 line:-1
it has this really important--


549
00:25:24.925 --> 00:25:27.027 line:-2 align:center
I shouldn't--
this isn't a "by the way."


550
00:25:27.060 --> 00:25:30.197 line:-2 align:center
