605
00:27:55,776 --> 00:27:58,045 line:-2
What the science
around meditation


606
00:27:58,078 --> 00:28:00,714 line:-1
is showing us, the neuroscience,


607
00:28:00,747 --> 00:28:04,251 line:-2
the looking into people's brains
and looking at what happens


608
00:28:04.284 --> 00:28:07.054 line:-2 align:center
when they meditate -
what this is showing us


609
00:28:07.087 --> 00:28:10.357 line:-1 align:center
is that happiness is a skill -


610
00:28:10,390 --> 00:28:15,062 line:-2
that the mind is trainable -
that all the things we want


611
00:28:15,095 --> 00:28:18,365 line:-2
can really be boiled down
to mind states.


612
00:28:18.398 --> 00:28:21.635 line:-2 align:center
We may think we want
professional success,


613
00:28:21.668 --> 00:28:26.607 line:-2 align:center
romantic success,
to get that new car,


614
00:28:26.640 --> 00:28:28.575 line:-1 align:center
to go on that big vacation,


615
00:28:28,609 --> 00:28:30,344 line:-2
all of which are fine
to have as goals,


616
00:28:30.377 --> 00:28:32.079 line:-2 align:center
but what we really want
are the mental states


617
00:28:32,112 --> 00:28:34,481 line:-1
that accompany those goals.


618
00:28:34.515 --> 00:28:36.216 line:-2 align:center
And as it turns out,
all of these


619
00:28:36.250 --> 00:28:41.154 line:-2 align:center
mental states--
calm, happiness, connection,


620
00:28:41.188 --> 00:28:44.725 line:-1 align:center
compassion, love--


621
00:28:44.758 --> 00:28:48.228 line:-1 align:center
these are trainable skills,


622
00:28:48,262 --> 00:28:51,498 line:-2
and meditation is one modality
through which you can do it,


623
00:28:51.532 --> 00:28:55.102 line:-2 align:center
so I really do encourage you
to give it a shot.


